# Djinn NETRUNNER (Cursor Rules)

Core identity: console-first, operator-centric appliance; logs are the primary progress visualization.

Non-negotiable constraints:
- Keep HTMX server-rendered UI; do not introduce a SPA framework.
- Keep styling in a single CSS file and minimal JS; do not split into component systems.
- Use PostgreSQL as the system-of-record for production (Docker Compose); SQLite is supported for local single-binary dev only.
- Avoid introducing external queues/caches (Redis is reserved, not required today).
- Preserve deterministic work: jobitems are durable plans created before execution; requeues resume and never regenerate.
- Preserve event-driven console updates via LISTEN/NOTIFY on PostgreSQL; avoid UI polling loops. SQLite dev may use worker polling instead of NOTIFY.

Docs to read before making changes:
- docs/MANIFEST.md
- docs/WHITEPAPER.md
- docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
- docs/UIIMPLEMENTATION.md
- docs/RUNBOOK.md
